M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 slightly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 184-189
) 0.55 mm long, moderately sclerotized. Apical process of median lobe trifid, much shorter than basal bulb, asymmetrically bent to left (dorsal view), inflexed ventrally; dorsal branches distinct, reaching level of tip of ventral branch in dorsal view, ventral branch oblique, with acute tip. Parameres in dorsal view narrowed posterior mid-length, slightly widened in middle part in lateral view. Internal sac complex, with apical sclerotized teeth, lateral row if spines, and squamous and denticular structures.
